1
00:00:37,333 --> 00:00:38,600
<i> That can't happen!</i>

2
00:00:38,733 --> 00:00:42,333
<i>If one of you has to disappear,
so you won't get back together,</i>

3
00:00:42,467 --> 00:00:43,567
<i> so you won't end up together,</i>

4
00:00:43,700 --> 00:00:45,033
<i>Fine! Choose,
which of the two of you</i>

5
00:00:45,167 --> 00:00:46,367
<i> I'll throw into hell.</i>

6
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:48,867
<i>The private investigator
emailed me.</i>

7
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:50,800
<i> Your dad could be in Bulacan.</i>

8
00:00:50,933 --> 00:00:52,933
<i> Felma and her kids won't stop.</i>

9
00:00:53,067 --> 00:00:54,800
<i> How long can you hide Manuel</i>

10
00:00:54,933 --> 00:00:56,300
<i>without getting traced by them?</i>

11
00:00:56,433 --> 00:00:57,500
<i> Not for long, Alice.</i>

12
00:00:57,633 --> 00:00:59,533
<i>Once Manuel's
condition improves,</i>

13
00:00:59,667 --> 00:01:01,433
<i>I will bring him back to Canada,
even if against his will.</i>

14
00:01:01,567 --> 00:01:05,033
<i>Dad, I'll find a way
to escape Mom.</i>

15
00:01:05,167 --> 00:01:06,233
<i> Hello, Uncle Abel?</i>

16
00:01:06,367 --> 00:01:07,400
<i> This is Jessica.</i>

17
00:01:07,567 --> 00:01:09,300
<i>Jessica?
Where are you now?</i>

18
00:01:09,433 --> 00:01:10,733
<i> Uncle, we're in Bulacan.</i>

19
00:01:10,867 --> 00:01:11,933
<i> Jessica!</i>

20
00:01:12,067 --> 00:01:13,233
<i> I'm sorry.</i>

21
00:01:13,367 --> 00:01:14,800
<i> Let's start over again.</i>

22
00:01:14,933 --> 00:01:17,867
<i> You, me, and Jessica.</i>

23
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:27,967
<i> No one else.</i>

24
00:01:34,133 --> 00:01:35,833
I'm sorry...

25
00:01:35,967 --> 00:01:38,500
my phone could only do so much.

26
00:01:38,633 --> 00:01:39,533
There's no signal there.

27
00:01:39,667 --> 00:01:41,267
You should've given it to me.

28
00:01:41,433 --> 00:01:43,533
I might be able to understand.

29
00:01:43,667 --> 00:01:45,100
Darling, you heard it.

30
00:01:45,233 --> 00:01:46,400
I was on speaker phone.

31
00:01:46,533 --> 00:01:48,600
Jessica has no signal.

32
00:01:48,733 --> 00:01:50,767
You don't clean your ear,
that's why.

33
00:01:50,900 --> 00:01:53,533
- The line was choppy.
- Wait, hold on.

34
00:01:53,667 --> 00:01:55,100
You might end up fighting.

35
00:01:56,167 --> 00:02:00,500
What matters is that we know
they're in Camalig.

36
00:02:00,633 --> 00:02:02,167
What is it again? Gu...

37
00:02:02,300 --> 00:02:04,667
- Gu Street? Nita's?
- Something like that.

38
00:02:04,800 --> 00:02:05,867
The internet says...

39
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:07,967
there's a Gulod Street
in Camalig, Meycauayan.

40
00:02:08,100 --> 00:02:10,000
- Ah.
- There!

41
00:02:10,133 --> 00:02:11,367
Maybe that's it!

42
00:02:11,500 --> 00:02:13,067
Uncle, let's go,
let's pick up Dad.

43
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:14,167
Son, hold on.

44
00:02:14,333 --> 00:02:16,167
Let's not be impulsive.

45
00:02:16,300 --> 00:02:18,267
We must plan it carefully.

46
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:19,300
Everything.

47
00:02:19,433 --> 00:02:20,767
Yes, Jeff.

48
00:02:20,900 --> 00:02:24,467
You have to bring Dad
back safely.

49
00:02:24,600 --> 00:02:26,767
You can't just use
your own car.

50
00:02:26,900 --> 00:02:28,200
Where will you put him?

51
00:02:28,333 --> 00:02:29,733
He won't fit there.

52
00:02:29,867 --> 00:02:32,167
Maybe we should use a van, Mom.

53
00:02:32,300 --> 00:02:34,600
Do we have one at FMP?

54
00:02:34,733 --> 00:02:38,067
We must ask for Colonel
Sarabia's help.

55
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:39,867
Mom, don't.

56
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:41,867
It's just Hazel who'll be
meeting us.

57
00:02:42,933 --> 00:02:44,233
I can face her myself.

58
00:02:44,367 --> 00:02:46,367
And Mom, this is personal
for me.

59
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:48,633
After what Dad did to me
and Andrea...

60
00:02:50,833 --> 00:02:52,233
<i> Help! Felma!</i>

61
00:02:52,367 --> 00:02:53,800
<i>Jeffrey, hold on!
Jeff!</i>

62
00:03:04,767 --> 00:03:06,533
<i> Dad!</i>

63
00:03:09,667 --> 00:03:11,933
<i> Dad! Dad!</i>

64
00:03:12,067 --> 00:03:14,200
<i>- Dad!
- Dad!</i>

65
00:03:14,333 --> 00:03:17,200
Mom, I can't just stand by
and do nothing to save Dad.

66
00:03:20,167 --> 00:03:22,033
That's why, Mom,
I want to make things right.

67
00:03:22,200 --> 00:03:23,800
I want to be the one
to bring him back.

68
00:03:23,933 --> 00:03:26,633
I'll be the one to bring
Dad home.

69
00:03:26,767 --> 00:03:28,500
All right, Jeff.

70
00:03:28,633 --> 00:03:30,533
Promise me, okay?

71
00:03:30,667 --> 00:03:32,267
Bring Dad home.

72
00:03:33,633 --> 00:03:35,233
Bring him back for me.

73
00:03:35,367 --> 00:03:37,200
Bring him back for all of us.

74
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:42,000
We can do this.

75
00:03:43,300 --> 00:03:44,167
Right, Uncle?

76
00:03:44,300 --> 00:03:45,200
Of course.

77
00:03:45,333 --> 00:03:47,667
I won't let Manuel down.

78
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:50,567
Need another hand?

79
00:03:50,700 --> 00:03:51,767
I'd like to come, too.

80
00:03:51,900 --> 00:03:54,167
Wait, Joel, your wound.

81
00:03:54,333 --> 00:03:55,300
I'm fine.

82
00:03:55,433 --> 00:03:57,233
I told you,
I'm not babying this.

83
00:03:57,367 --> 00:03:59,700
I have a friend
with a large van.

84
00:03:59,833 --> 00:04:01,067
We can use it.

85
00:05:09,800 --> 00:05:19,767
Who did you call?

86
00:05:21,333 --> 00:05:22,600
No one, Mom.

87
00:05:33,233 --> 00:05:34,700
You're clever, right?

88
00:05:34,867 --> 00:05:37,267
You even erased the number?

89
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:38,967
I didn't call anyone.

90
00:05:39,100 --> 00:05:40,867
I was just about to call,

91
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:43,267
but I heard you come downstairs.

92
00:05:46,100 --> 00:05:48,167
You were still trying
to call someone!

93
00:05:48,300 --> 00:05:49,833
How many times are you going
to betray me, Jessica?

94
00:05:49,967 --> 00:05:51,233
- Huh?
- Mom, you're hurting me!

95
00:05:51,367 --> 00:05:52,867
- Mom!
- You traitor!

96
00:05:54,167 --> 00:05:55,200
My own daughter!

97
00:05:56,467 --> 00:05:57,600
- Mom!
- What now?

98
00:05:57,733 --> 00:05:58,800
Still won't admit it?

99
00:05:58,933 --> 00:06:00,700
You're betraying me again,
aren't you?

100
00:06:00,833 --> 00:06:02,233
How many times
do I have to tell you?

101
00:06:02,367 --> 00:06:03,967
Why are you like this, huh?

102
00:06:04,100 --> 00:06:05,033
Hazel, stop it!

103
00:06:05,167 --> 00:06:06,300
You're making me angry!

104
00:06:06,433 --> 00:06:07,967
- Mom!
- No! You're so stubborn!

105
00:06:08,133 --> 00:06:09,267
So darn stubborn!

106
00:06:09,400 --> 00:06:10,667
Mom!

107
00:06:11,800 --> 00:06:14,500
Mom, stop!

108
00:06:14,633 --> 00:06:16,567
I'm your mother.

109
00:06:16,700 --> 00:06:18,567
I raised you, fed you,

110
00:06:18,700 --> 00:06:21,133
sent you to school,
and this is how you repay me?

111
00:06:21,267 --> 00:06:22,433
Why?

112
00:06:22,567 --> 00:06:23,300
Come here!

113
00:06:23,433 --> 00:06:24,767
- You did nothing...
- Oh...

114
00:06:24,900 --> 00:06:26,467
Mom, please stop!

115
00:06:27,500 --> 00:06:29,067
Don't hurt Jessica!

116
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:31,200
Hazel!

117
00:06:31,333 --> 00:06:32,767
You're always going against me!

118
00:06:32,900 --> 00:06:33,900
Why?

119
00:06:34,033 --> 00:06:35,333
You're so hardheaded!

120
00:06:35,467 --> 00:06:36,900
- Stop it!
- What?

121
00:06:37,033 --> 00:06:38,667
Always the same!

122
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:40,433
Always you who drags me down!

123
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:42,200
You! It's always you!

124
00:06:42,333 --> 00:06:43,967
- Mommy!
- No! What, huh?!

125
00:06:44,700 --> 00:06:46,000
You're taking her side now?

126
00:06:46,133 --> 00:06:47,867
I don't know you!

127
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:49,233
- You're always like this!
- Hazel!

128
00:06:49,367 --> 00:06:50,433
Why are you like this, Jessica?

129
00:06:50,567 --> 00:06:52,200
Why?

130
00:06:52,333 --> 00:06:53,333
Dad!

131
00:06:53,467 --> 00:06:54,567
Manuel?

132
00:06:54,700 --> 00:06:55,667
- Dad!
- Manuel!

133
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:57,167
Dad!

134
00:06:57,300 --> 00:06:58,467
Manuel!

135
00:07:06,867 --> 00:07:08,267
- Manuel! What happened?
- Dad! Dad!

136
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:10,333
Huh? What happened to you?
Why did you fall down?

137
00:07:10,467 --> 00:07:11,467
Wait.

138
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:12,967
Jessica, what are you
staring at?

139
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:14,133
Come on, help me!

140
00:07:14,300 --> 00:07:15,700
Wait, just hold on.

141
00:07:15,833 --> 00:07:17,000
Hold on, Manuel.

142
00:07:17,133 --> 00:07:18,700
You'll get hurt, wait.

143
00:07:18,833 --> 00:07:20,567
Slowly! Over there!

144
00:07:20,700 --> 00:07:22,067
Manuel!

145
00:07:23,100 --> 00:07:24,000
Once we get Dad,

146
00:07:24,133 --> 00:07:26,333
we'll head straight
to the hospital, okay?

147
00:07:26,467 --> 00:07:28,300
So the doctor can check
his condition.

148
00:07:28,433 --> 00:07:31,267
All right, Son,
We'll wait for you there, okay?

149
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:33,067
Jeff, maybe I should come, too?

150
00:07:33,200 --> 00:07:35,767
Andrea, no, we can move faster
if it's just us.

151
00:07:35,900 --> 00:07:37,267
Stay with Mom instead, okay?

152
00:07:38,267 --> 00:07:40,500
What time should
we leave tomorrow?

153
00:07:40,633 --> 00:07:41,633
Around 10 in the morning.

154
00:07:41,767 --> 00:07:42,867
The van's ready by then.

155
00:07:44,200 --> 00:07:45,333
Joel, thank you, okay?

156
00:07:45,467 --> 00:07:46,800
Thank you.

157
00:07:48,700 --> 00:07:50,500
Oh, sweetie, why?

158
00:07:51,600 --> 00:07:55,100
I'm just happy because
I'll see Dad tomorrow.

159
00:07:57,400 --> 00:07:59,100
Dear.

160
00:08:01,467 --> 00:08:11,233
Come here.

161
00:08:11,367 --> 00:08:13,167
Stop crying.

162
00:08:25,167 --> 00:08:26,600
Manuel.

163
00:08:28,233 --> 00:08:29,900
How are you feeling?

164
00:08:30,033 --> 00:08:31,900
Dear, what hurts?

165
00:08:33,700 --> 00:08:35,067
Huh?

166
00:08:43,033 --> 00:08:45,567
You're ruthless, Hazel!

167
00:08:45,700 --> 00:08:47,433
You never get tired, huh?

168
00:08:47,567 --> 00:08:50,467
How long are you going to keep
hurting my child?

169
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:52,200
Until she learns to respect me.

170
00:08:54,033 --> 00:08:56,400
So she'll learn
not to betray me.

171
00:08:57,467 --> 00:08:59,800
Hazel, she's not betraying you.

172
00:08:59,933 --> 00:09:01,700
What do you call
what she's doing?

173
00:09:02,567 --> 00:09:04,267
Hazel, that's love.

174
00:09:05,567 --> 00:09:07,467
My child loves me deeply.

175
00:09:09,767 --> 00:09:12,000
That's why she defends me
against you.

176
00:09:12,133 --> 00:09:13,233
Come on.

177
00:09:13,367 --> 00:09:15,667
For heaven's sake, Hazel,
just hurt me!

178
00:09:16,867 --> 00:09:18,767
- Hurt me instead!
- Dad, Dad,

179
00:09:18,900 --> 00:09:20,933
Your wound might hurt again.

180
00:09:22,067 --> 00:09:24,100
- Dad.
- Love?

181
00:09:26,167 --> 00:09:27,267
How about me, Manuel?

182
00:09:28,333 --> 00:09:29,867
When will you ever love me?

183
00:09:31,067 --> 00:09:32,733
Never.

184
00:09:32,867 --> 00:09:34,500
I can't love you anymore.

185
00:09:36,133 --> 00:09:37,600
Why, Manuel?

186
00:09:39,533 --> 00:09:42,133
I almost begged for your love.

187
00:09:43,333 --> 00:09:45,100
I did everything.

188
00:09:46,067 --> 00:09:47,367
Everything.

189
00:09:48,900 --> 00:09:50,633
And you still can't love me?

190
00:09:51,867 --> 00:09:53,600
Why?

191
00:09:53,733 --> 00:09:57,100
Because love can't be forced.

192
00:10:05,333 --> 00:10:06,767
Okay.

193
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:09,433
Fine.

194
00:10:11,833 --> 00:10:13,833
I won't force it, fine.

195
00:10:15,333 --> 00:10:18,200
But we won't be apart.

196
00:10:18,333 --> 00:10:20,800
Whether you like it or not,

197
00:10:20,933 --> 00:10:22,667
I'll bring you back to Canada.

198
00:10:23,833 --> 00:10:26,100
Go alone, we won't come
with you.

199
00:10:29,767 --> 00:10:31,500
You will, Manuel.

200
00:10:31,633 --> 00:10:33,200
You will.

201
00:10:35,400 --> 00:10:37,533
You won't make me agree, Hazel.

202
00:10:38,667 --> 00:10:40,000
And once I recover,

203
00:10:41,133 --> 00:10:42,967
Jessica and I
will leave you, too.

204
00:10:49,233 --> 00:10:50,667
Recover?

205
00:10:51,700 --> 00:10:53,800
Who said you're going
to get better?

206
00:10:54,700 --> 00:10:56,800
Maybe you forgot, Manuel.

207
00:10:58,600 --> 00:11:00,467
I'm the one giving you
your medicine, right?

208
00:11:02,433 --> 00:11:04,567
I know about medicine.

209
00:11:04,700 --> 00:11:07,167
If I can heal,

210
00:11:07,300 --> 00:11:09,167
I can also cause pain.

211
00:11:09,333 --> 00:11:10,433
Mom!

212
00:11:10,567 --> 00:11:12,067
You're ruthless, Hazel!

213
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:13,267
Dad.

214
00:11:13,400 --> 00:11:15,100
- Ruthless!
- Dad!

215
00:11:15,233 --> 00:11:17,067
Ruthless!

216
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:20,700
<i>Why does my head feel so heavy?</i>

217
00:11:20,833 --> 00:11:23,600
<i>And I'm sleepy, I just woke up.</i>

218
00:11:23,733 --> 00:11:24,933
<i> It's okay.</i>

219
00:11:25,067 --> 00:11:26,433
<i>It's just the effect of the
medicine.</i>

220
00:11:27,533 --> 00:11:28,700
Ruthless!

221
00:11:29,733 --> 00:11:31,067
You're a monster!

222
00:11:33,533 --> 00:11:35,433
You're a monster, Hazel!

223
00:11:40,067 --> 00:11:42,367
Monster!

224
00:11:48,100 --> 00:11:50,533
Joel, are you sure
you can go tomorrow?

225
00:11:52,033 --> 00:11:53,867
Yes, I'm okay.

226
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:54,867
I can do it.

227
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:57,567
You've always been there for me.

228
00:11:57,700 --> 00:12:01,367
Even now, helping us
bring Dad back...

229
00:12:01,500 --> 00:12:03,533
you're still here.

230
00:12:03,667 --> 00:12:05,367
Andrea...

231
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:08,600
I'll do everything...

232
00:12:09,733 --> 00:12:10,867
for you.

233
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:13,300
Thank you, thank you, Joel.

234
00:12:14,100 --> 00:12:15,533
I'll get going, okay?

235
00:12:15,667 --> 00:12:16,667
Bye.

236
00:12:17,800 --> 00:12:19,567
I got it, I got it.

237
00:12:20,967 --> 00:12:21,867
Thank you.

238
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:26,533
- Take care.
- Bye, bye, okay.

239
00:12:28,633 --> 00:12:30,167
Bye!

240
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:44,567
What, Sweetie?

241
00:12:45,633 --> 00:12:51,667
Are you looking for a falling
star to make a wish again?

242
00:12:52,700 --> 00:12:54,600
Yup.

243
00:12:54,733 --> 00:12:59,467
I'll wish for Jeff to bring Dad
home safely tomorrow.

244
00:13:01,433 --> 00:13:05,133
Sweetie, you don't need to wish.

245
00:13:06,233 --> 00:13:07,800
It's going to happen.

246
00:13:08,333 --> 00:13:09,867
Okay?

247
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:12,467
Do you think Dad will bring
Jessica along?

248
00:13:13,867 --> 00:13:15,167
I think so.

249
00:13:17,067 --> 00:13:19,633
She called Uncle Abel.

250
00:13:19,767 --> 00:13:21,033
That means...

251
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:24,500
she wants to be far
from Hazel, too.

252
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:27,900
Coleen...

253
00:13:28,033 --> 00:13:32,700
whatever problem you
and Jessica had...

254
00:13:32,833 --> 00:13:33,800
be the big person,

255
00:13:33,933 --> 00:13:36,567
be the one to apologize
when she gets back, okay?

256
00:13:36,700 --> 00:13:38,700
She's our sibling.

257
00:13:38,833 --> 00:13:40,733
The youngest.

258
00:13:42,233 --> 00:13:44,033
And remember...

259
00:13:45,367 --> 00:13:48,100
she's the bridge that brought
you closer to Dad.

260
00:13:56,600 --> 00:13:58,367
You know what, sis?
I'm happy.

261
00:13:59,400 --> 00:14:02,300
Finally, the kids will get
Manuel back

262
00:14:02,433 --> 00:14:06,333
from that evil dwarf.

263
00:14:12,533 --> 00:14:13,833
But, you know, sis...

264
00:14:13,967 --> 00:14:15,633
I can't help but wonder.

265
00:14:18,467 --> 00:14:21,200
It seems like you'll never
have peace.

266
00:14:21,333 --> 00:14:25,667
Right? that Hazel will keep
messing with you.

267
00:14:25,800 --> 00:14:28,433
She won't stop chasing

268
00:14:28,600 --> 00:14:31,133
because she's the real wife.

269
00:14:32,367 --> 00:14:35,033
What if she files
a case against you?

270
00:14:35,167 --> 00:14:36,800
She can do it if she wants.

271
00:14:37,867 --> 00:14:41,567
That's better, so we'll see
each other in court.

272
00:14:43,267 --> 00:14:44,833
What she did...

273
00:14:46,233 --> 00:14:48,267
- was kidnapping.
- Right.

274
00:14:48,400 --> 00:14:50,467
- Illegal detention.
- Right.

275
00:14:51,500 --> 00:14:53,133
That's what Attorney Yeban said.

276
00:14:54,533 --> 00:14:57,367
Just one testimony
from Manuel...

277
00:14:57,500 --> 00:14:59,533
and Jessica...

278
00:14:59,667 --> 00:15:01,467
and the case is over.

279
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:04,867
And you, sis, what's your plan?

280
00:15:07,100 --> 00:15:12,967
I'll help Manuel speed up his
annulment with Hazel.

281
00:15:15,267 --> 00:15:17,400
I'll take him back
from that woman.

282
00:15:19,567 --> 00:15:20,767
Wow!

283
00:15:20,900 --> 00:15:25,267
Sis... you're a whole different
person now.

284
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:30,533
Felma, fierce, version 2.0.

285
00:15:31,133 --> 00:15:32,600
Come on, stop it.

286
00:15:35,667 --> 00:15:37,767
I'm the one Manuel loves.

287
00:15:39,700 --> 00:15:42,067
I'm just holding myself back.

288
00:15:42,867 --> 00:15:45,000
Because I don't want to be the
other woman.

289
00:15:48,533 --> 00:15:49,567
But...

290
00:15:49,700 --> 00:15:51,200
he's doing everything...

291
00:15:52,567 --> 00:15:54,633
to get back with me.

292
00:15:56,800 --> 00:15:58,767
I'm so tired...

293
00:15:58,900 --> 00:16:01,233
of denying how I feel.

294
00:16:03,767 --> 00:16:06,867
Sis, I'll fight for my love
for Manuel

295
00:16:07,233 --> 00:16:10,800
because Hazel only
has a piece of paper.

296
00:16:11,867 --> 00:16:12,867
I have...

297
00:16:14,400 --> 00:16:15,867
his heart.

298
00:16:19,867 --> 00:16:21,967
I've got your back, Sis.

299
00:16:23,200 --> 00:16:25,933
I saw how you started.

300
00:16:26,067 --> 00:16:27,467
You were even denying it to me.

301
00:16:27,600 --> 00:16:30,267
You're such an in-denial frog.

302
00:16:30,400 --> 00:16:31,967
I know you love him, too.

303
00:16:34,400 --> 00:16:36,233
- I love you, Sis.
- I love you too.

304
00:16:36,367 --> 00:16:38,033
Thank you, my friend.

305
00:16:40,167 --> 00:16:44,867
From then until now,
you've always been there

306
00:16:45,033 --> 00:16:46,800
to support me.

307
00:16:46,933 --> 00:16:48,300
Thank you.

308
00:16:48,433 --> 00:16:51,000
Always, Sis,
always.

309
00:16:51,133 --> 00:16:54,233
You know, Uncle, I kind of wish
I could speed up time.

310
00:16:55,833 --> 00:16:57,233
You know, it's like...

311
00:16:58,167 --> 00:16:59,767
I wish tomorrow would come.

312
00:17:00,633 --> 00:17:02,533
I'm excited to see Dad.

313
00:17:04,233 --> 00:17:07,300
If Manuel hears
what you're saying,

314
00:17:08,067 --> 00:17:09,800
he'll cry again.

315
00:17:11,367 --> 00:17:14,733
You know, godchild, when we were
in Saudi Arabia,

316
00:17:16,333 --> 00:17:19,367
your dad cried almost every day.

317
00:17:20,433 --> 00:17:23,400
You were always
in our conversations.

318
00:17:24,100 --> 00:17:26,667
He kept saying how much
he missed you guys

319
00:17:26,800 --> 00:17:29,333
and how much he loved you.

320
00:17:30,567 --> 00:17:33,333
So I'm so happy
you'll be together again.

321
00:17:35,600 --> 00:17:45,400
Thank you, Uncle.

322
00:17:57,967 --> 00:17:59,433
Mom...

323
00:17:59,567 --> 00:18:01,967
why isn't there
breakfast for Dad?

324
00:18:05,133 --> 00:18:07,267
He doesn't need breakfast
or lunch.

325
00:18:07,400 --> 00:18:08,400
What?

326
00:18:09,433 --> 00:18:12,167
Did you give him medicine?

327
00:18:12,300 --> 00:18:14,267
Are you seriously going
to make him sick?

328
00:18:14,400 --> 00:18:15,467
Relax!

329
00:18:15,600 --> 00:18:17,467
Your reaction is a bit much.

330
00:18:17,600 --> 00:18:19,933
I just gave him a sedative.

331
00:18:20,067 --> 00:18:22,300
And I don't want you
talking to him.

332
00:18:22,467 --> 00:18:24,633
You might badmouth me
to him again.

333
00:18:24,767 --> 00:18:27,367
I'm not badmouthing you to Dad.

334
00:18:27,733 --> 00:18:28,767
Come on, Jessica.

335
00:18:28,900 --> 00:18:30,533
You're annoying me so early
in the morning.

336
00:18:34,767 --> 00:18:36,300
Oh, by the way...

337
00:18:36,433 --> 00:18:38,133
Give me your passports.

338
00:18:39,100 --> 00:18:41,667
I'm booking our flight
back to Canada.

339
00:18:45,100 --> 00:18:46,367
Oh?

340
00:18:48,767 --> 00:18:50,267
What's that?

341
00:18:50,400 --> 00:18:52,367
Why did you grin at me?

342
00:18:52,500 --> 00:18:53,700
Where's the passport?

343
00:18:54,900 --> 00:18:57,167
You can't bring us back
to Canada, Mom.

344
00:18:57,300 --> 00:18:59,800
Our passports aren't here.

345
00:19:00,333 --> 00:19:01,533
What?

346
00:19:01,667 --> 00:19:03,267
Where are they?

347
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:06,033
At Auntie Felma's house.

348
00:19:12,233 --> 00:19:13,567
Hey, stop messing with me.

349
00:19:14,133 --> 00:19:16,167
Do you want to get hurt again?

350
00:19:16,300 --> 00:19:17,433
You're going to hurt me?

351
00:19:17,800 --> 00:19:20,000
For what? For telling the truth?

352
00:19:21,133 --> 00:19:23,567
Have you forgotten that you used
Dad's permanent resident card

353
00:19:23,700 --> 00:19:27,800
and driver's license for his
health insurance?

354
00:19:29,167 --> 00:19:31,633
Dad's passport isn't here.

355
00:19:31,767 --> 00:19:34,200
I left it when I grabbed
our things

356
00:19:34,333 --> 00:19:36,367
because Coleen
and I were arguing.

357
00:19:37,600 --> 00:19:39,500
So if you don't believe me,

358
00:19:39,633 --> 00:19:41,467
call Auntie Felma.

359
00:19:41,600 --> 00:19:44,700
She'll find
where our passport is.

360
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:50,833
Didang, make sure this is
spotless, okay?

361
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:53,000
Yes, Ma'am.

362
00:19:53,133 --> 00:19:54,033
I know.

363
00:19:54,167 --> 00:19:56,233
I'll clean this thoroughly.

364
00:19:57,133 --> 00:20:00,500
You could just leave me
alone, though.

365
00:20:00,633 --> 00:20:03,100
I mean, you don't have
to watch over me.

366
00:20:03,267 --> 00:20:04,600
Sorry.

367
00:20:04,733 --> 00:20:06,900
I just want it perfectly clean

368
00:20:07,033 --> 00:20:09,367
because Manuel's going
to recover here.

369
00:20:09,500 --> 00:20:11,833
Yes, I get it, Ma'am.

370
00:20:11,967 --> 00:20:14,667
You could find
something else to do.

371
00:20:14,800 --> 00:20:17,667
Even if it's just me here,
leave this to me, Ma'am.

372
00:20:25,667 --> 00:20:29,167
Manuel and Jessica left
some stuff behind.

373
00:20:36,567 --> 00:20:38,233
What are you waiting for, Ma'am?

374
00:20:38,367 --> 00:20:39,400
Hug it.

375
00:20:40,800 --> 00:20:42,000
Hug it?

376
00:20:42,133 --> 00:20:45,567
Ma'am... isn't it like
in the movies?

377
00:20:45,700 --> 00:20:48,000
When the hero is separated
from their loved one,

378
00:20:48,133 --> 00:20:50,800
then sees a personal item...

379
00:20:50,933 --> 00:20:52,267
they hug it...

380
00:20:53,367 --> 00:20:54,800
cry...

381
00:20:54,933 --> 00:20:56,767
then have a moment.

382
00:20:58,433 --> 00:20:59,200
Didang!

383
00:20:59,333 --> 00:21:01,067
You're crazy!

384
00:21:01,200 --> 00:21:02,400
Come on!

385
00:21:02,533 --> 00:21:06,167
They only do that when their
loved one dies.

386
00:21:06,300 --> 00:21:07,400
Is that how it works?

387
00:21:15,167 --> 00:21:16,433
What's this in here?

388
00:21:17,833 --> 00:21:21,400
Oh! The passports
were left behind.

389
00:21:21,533 --> 00:21:23,467
Oh, this is Jessica's.

390
00:21:25,767 --> 00:21:26,933
And Manuel's.

391
00:21:29,500 --> 00:21:31,800
<i> You're going home now, Manuel.</i>

392
00:21:31,933 --> 00:21:34,867
<i>You're going home to me
and your children.</i>

393
00:21:40,200 --> 00:21:42,267
Don't celebrate yet, Jessica.

394
00:21:46,367 --> 00:21:48,167
I can easily ask
the Canadian Embassy

395
00:21:48,300 --> 00:21:51,067
how to replace your passports.

396
00:22:02,967 --> 00:22:04,800
- Ma'am.
- Ah!

397
00:22:04,933 --> 00:22:07,400
In the movies, the hero...

398
00:22:07,533 --> 00:22:12,567
kisses the picture when they
see it, even if it's tiny.

399
00:22:12,700 --> 00:22:14,800
Didang, stop it already!

400
00:22:14,933 --> 00:22:18,133
Come on! Finish cleaning,
keep going.

401
00:22:18,300 --> 00:22:19,733
You're something else, Didang.

402
00:22:19,867 --> 00:22:20,967
- Oh, Son.
- We're leaving now.

403
00:22:21,100 --> 00:22:22,967
Joel's outside.

404
00:22:23,100 --> 00:22:24,167
All right, Dear.

405
00:22:24,300 --> 00:22:26,700
Felma, someone texted me early
this morning.

406
00:22:26,833 --> 00:22:28,600
I don't know if it's a prank
or real.

407
00:22:28,733 --> 00:22:29,867
It's an address.

408
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:32,733
Maybe Jessica and Manuel
are there.

409
00:22:34,800 --> 00:22:36,267
Okay, be careful.

410
00:22:36,400 --> 00:22:37,433
We'll try it first.

411
00:22:37,567 --> 00:22:39,900
Don't worry, I'll take care
of my godchild.

412
00:22:40,033 --> 00:22:42,133
- Thanks.
- I'll get them home safely.

413
00:22:42,267 --> 00:22:43,833
Thanks, take care, okay?

414
00:22:43,967 --> 00:22:45,033
Take care, son.

415
00:22:45,167 --> 00:22:47,467
- Take care!
- Okay, Mom.

416
00:22:47,600 --> 00:22:49,133
- Take care!
- Yes, Mom.

417
00:22:54,600 --> 00:22:56,433
Mom, what time will you be home?

418
00:22:58,033 --> 00:22:59,233
I don't know.

419
00:23:04,700 --> 00:23:06,800
Mommy, I don't have lunch.

420
00:23:06,933 --> 00:23:11,000
Can you give me some money
to buy something outside?

421
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:14,367
Do you think I'd trust you
to go out?

422
00:23:16,500 --> 00:23:18,533
There's rice and canned food.

423
00:23:18,667 --> 00:23:20,167
Cook the rice, cook food.

424
00:23:23,400 --> 00:23:24,967
Go on.

425
00:23:25,100 --> 00:23:26,100
Go check on your dad first.

426
00:23:26,233 --> 00:23:27,533
Maybe he needs something.

427
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:30,700
Yes, Mommy.

428
00:24:18,267 --> 00:24:19,233
Good day.

429
00:24:19,367 --> 00:24:22,200
Do you know where the
Capistrano's house is?

430
00:24:22,333 --> 00:24:25,967
There!
That brown old gate.

431
00:24:26,100 --> 00:24:26,967
Big brother Jeffrey!

432
00:24:27,100 --> 00:24:28,633
- Oh, Jessica!
- Are you okay?

433
00:24:28,800 --> 00:24:30,567
Mommy isn't here.

434
00:24:30,700 --> 00:24:32,933
Get Dad ready, okay?

435
00:24:33,067 --> 00:24:35,533
Look at this,
the insurance form.

436
00:24:35,667 --> 00:24:38,000
The end of the signature
goes up.

437
00:24:39,400 --> 00:24:43,267
But in this discharge form,
the end goes down.

438
00:24:43,400 --> 00:24:45,633
So you're saying
this is forgery?

439
00:24:48,967 --> 00:24:50,167
Darn it!

440
00:24:50,300 --> 00:24:52,267
Where are you taking Manuel?
Where are you taking Manuel?

441
00:24:52,400 --> 00:24:54,433
Can't we just call them?

442
00:24:54,567 --> 00:24:56,533
Coleen, remember the plan?

443
00:24:56,667 --> 00:24:59,633
They're supposed to call us so
they won't be disrupted.

444
00:24:59,767 --> 00:25:00,900
Joel's calling, dear.

445
00:25:02,867 --> 00:25:04,367
Hello, Joel?
